obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (80942)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80942&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Mediation Act, 2023.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall extend to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1 as the Central Government may, by notification, appoint`
  line `and different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act and any reference in any such`
  line `provision to the commencement of this Act shall be construed as a reference to the coming into force`
  line `of that provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 9th day of October, 2023, vide notification No. S.O. 4384(E), for Ss.1, 3, 26, Ss.31 to 38 (both inclusive), Ss. 45 to 47 (both`
  line `inclusive), Ss. 50 to 54 (both inclusive), and Ss.56 to 57 (both inclusive), dated 9th October, 2023 see Gazette of India,`
  line `Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (80943)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Application.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80943&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `This Act shall apply where mediation is conducted in India, and--`
  line
  line `(i) all or both parties habitually reside in or are incorporated in or have their place of business`
  line `in India; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the mediation agreement provides that any dispute shall be resolved in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(iii) there is an international mediation; or`
  line
  line `(iv) wherein one of the parties to the dispute is the Central Government or a State Government`
  line `or agencies, public bodies, corporations and local bodies, including entities controlled or owned by`
  line `such Government and where the matter pertains to a commercial dispute; or`
  line
  line `(v) to any other kind of dispute if deemed appropriate and notified by the Central Government`
  line `or a State Government from time to time, for resolution through mediation under this Act, wherein`
  line `such Governments, or agencies, public bodies, corporations and local bodies including entities`
  line `controlled or owned by them, is a party.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (80944)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80944&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires, --`
  line
  line `(a) "commercial dispute" means a dispute defined in clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 2 of`
  line `the Commercial Courts Act, 2015 (4 of 2016);`
  line
  line `(b) "community mediator" means a mediator for the purposes of conduct of community mediation`
  line `under Chapter X;`
  line
  line `(c) "Council" means the Mediation Council of India established under section 31;`
  line
  line `(d) "court" means the competent court in India having pecuniary and territorial jurisdiction and`
  line `having jurisdiction to decide the disputes forming the subject matter of mediation, if the same had`
  line `been the subject matter of a suit or proceeding;`
  line
  line `(e) "court-annexed mediation" means mediation including pre-litigation mediation conducted at the`
  line `mediation centres established by any court or tribunal;`
  line
  line `(f) "institutional mediation" means mediation conducted under the aegis of a mediation service`
  line provider;
  line
  line `(g) "international mediation" means mediation undertaken under this Act and relates to a`
  line `commercial dispute arising out of a legal relationship, contractual or otherwise, under any law for the`
  line `time being in force in India, and where at least one of the parties, is.--`
  line
  line `(i) an individual who is a national of, or habitually resides in, any country other than India; or`
  line
  line `(ii) a body corporate including a Limited Liability Partnership of any nature, with its place of`
  line `business outside India; or`
  line
  line `(iii) an association or body of individuals whose place of business is outside India; or`
  line
  line `(iv) the Government of a foreign country;`
  line
  line `(h) "mediation" includes a process, whether referred to by the expression mediation, pre-litigation`
  line `mediation, online mediation, community mediation, conciliation or an expression of similar import,`
  line `whereby parties attempt to reach an amicable settlement of their dispute with the assistance of a third`
  line `person referred to as mediator, who does not have the authority to impose a settlement upon the parties`
  line `to the dispute;`
  line
  line `(i) "mediator" means a person who is appointed to be a mediator, by the parties or by a mediation`
  line `service provider, to undertake mediation, and includes a person registered as mediator with the`
  line Council.
  line
  line `Explanation.--Where more than one mediator is appointed for a mediation, reference to a mediator`
  line `under this Act shall be a reference to all the mediators;`
  line
  line `(j) "mediation agreement" means a mediation agreement referred to in sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 4;`
  line
  line `(k) "mediation communication" means communication made, whether in electronic form or`
  line `otherwise, through--`
  line
  line `(i) anything said or done;`
  line
  line `(ii) any document; or`
  line
  line `(iii) any information provided,`
  line
  line `for the purposes of, or in relation to, or in the course of mediation, and includes a mediation`
  line `agreement or a mediated settlement agreement;`
  line
  line `(l) "mediation institute" means a body or organisation that provides training, continuous education`
  line `and certification of mediators and carries out such other functions under this Act;`
  line
  line `(m) "mediation service provider" means a mediation service provider referred to in sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 40;`
  line
  line `(n) "mediated settlement agreement" means mediated settlement agreement referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 19;`
  line
  line `(o) "Member" means a Full-Time or Part-Time Member of the Council and includes the`
  line Chairperson;
  line
  line `(p) "notification" means notification published in the Official Gazette and the expression`
  line `"notified" with its cognate meanings and grammatical variations shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(q) "online mediation" means online mediation referred to in section 30;`
  line
  line `(r) "participants" means persons other than the parties who participate in the mediation and`
  line `includes advisers, advocates, consultants and any technical experts and observers;`
  line
  line `(s) "party" means a party to a mediation agreement or mediation proceeding whose agreement or`
  line `consent is necessary to resolve the dispute and includes their successors;`
  line
  line `(t) "place of business" includes--`
  line
  line `(a) a place from where the business is ordinarily carried on, and includes a warehouse, a`
  line `godown or any other place where a party stores it's goods, supplies or receives goods or services or`
  line `both; or`
  line
  line `(b) a place where a party maintains its books of account; or`
  line
  line `(c) a place where a party is engaged in business through an agent, by whatever name called;`
  line
  line `(u) "pre-litigation mediation" means a process of undertaking mediation, as provided under`
  line `section 5, for settlement of disputes prior to the filing of a suit or proceeding of civil or commercial`
  line `nature in respect thereof, before a court or notified tribunal under sub-section (2) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(v) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made by the Central Government under this Act;`
  line
  line `(w) "Schedule" means the Schedule annexed to this Act;`
  line
  line `(x) "secure electronic signature" with reference to online mediation means, electronic signatures`
  line `referred to in section 15 of the Information Technology Act, 2000 (21 of 2000); and`
  line
  line `(y) "specified" means specified by regulations made by the Council under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (80945)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Mediation agreement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80945&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) A mediation agreement shall be in writing, by or between parties`
  line `and anyone claiming through them, to submit to mediation all or certain disputes which have arisen or`
  line `which may arise between the parties.`
  line
  line `(2) A mediation agreement may be in the form of a mediation clause in a contract or in the form of`
  line `a separate agreement.`
  line
  line `(3) A mediation agreement is in writing, if it is contained in or recorded as--`
  line
  line `(a) any document signed by the parties;`
  line
  line `(b) an exchange of communications or letters including through electronic form as provided`
  line `under the Information Technology Act, 2000 (21 of 2000);`
  line
  line `(c) any pleadings in a suit or any other proceedings in which existence of mediation agreement`
  line `is alleged by one party and not denied by the other.`
  line
  line `(4) A reference in any agreement containing a mediation clause shall constitute a mediation`
  line `agreement if the agreement is in writing and the reference is such as to make the mediation clause as`
  line `part of the agreement.`
  line
  line `(5) The parties may agree to submit to mediation any dispute arising between them under an`
  line `agreement, whether entered prior to arising of the dispute or subsequent thereto.`
  line
  line `(6) A mediation agreement in case of international mediation shall refer to an agreement for`
  line `resolution in matters of commercial disputes referred to in clause (a) of section 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (80946)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Pre-litigation mediation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80946&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to other provisions of this Act, whether any mediation`
  line `agreement exists or not, the parties before filing any suit or proceedings of civil or commercial nature in any court, may voluntarily and with mutual consent take steps to settle the disputes by pre-litigation`
  line `mediation in accordance with the provisions of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that pre-litigation mediation in matters of commercial disputes of Specified Value shall`
  line `be undertaken in accordance with the provisions of section 12A of the Commercial Courts Act,`
  line `2015 (4 of 2016), and the rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall be applicable to the tribunals notified by the Central`
  line `Government or a State Government, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of sub-sections (1) and (2), unless otherwise agreed upon by the parties, a`
  line mediator,--
  line
  line `(i) registered with the Council; or`
  line
  line `(ii) empanelled by a court-annexed mediation centre; or`
  line
  line `(iii) empanelled by an Authority constituted under the Legal Services Authorities Act,`
  line `1987 (39 of 1987); or`
  line
  line `(iv) empanelled by a mediation service provider recognised under this Act,`
  line `shall conduct pre-litigation mediation.`
  line
  line `(4) For conducting pre-litigation mediation under clauses (ii) and (iii) of sub-section (3), a party`
  line `may request any person designated for this purpose by the High Courts, or an Authority constituted`
  line `under the Legal Services Authorities Act, 1987 (39 of 1987), as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(5) The court-annexed mediation centre and an Authority constituted under the Legal Services`
  line `Authorities Act, 1987 (39 of 1987), shall maintain a panel of mediators for the purposes of`
  line `pre-litigation mediation.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and (2) and the Motor Vehicles Act,`
  line `1988 (59 of 1988), when an application for compensation arising out of an accident is made before the`
  line `Claims Tribunal, if the settlement as provided for in section 149 of that Act is not arrived at between`
  line `the parties, the Claims Tribunal shall refer the parties for mediation to a mediator or mediation service`
  line `provider under this Act.`
  line
  line `(7) Where the parties arrive at a settlement agreement under sub-section (6), it shall be placed`
  line `before the Claims Tribunal for its consideration.`
  line
  line `(8) If the parties do not reach to settlement agreement under sub-section (6), a non-settlement`
  line `report prepared by the mediator shall be forwarded to the Claims Tribunal, which has referred the`
  line `matter for mediation, for adjudication.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (80947)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Disputes or matters not fit for mediation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80947&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) A mediation under this Act shall not be`
  line `conducted for resolution of any dispute or matter contained in the indicative list under the First`
  line `Schedule:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained herein shall prevent any court, if deemed appropriate, from`
  line `referring any dispute relating to compoundable offences including the matrimonial offences which are`
  line `compoundable and pending between the parties, to mediation:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the outcome of such mediation shall not be deemed to be a judgment or`
  line `decree of court referred to in sub-section (2) of section 27, and shall be further considered by the court`
  line `in accordance with the law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Central Government is satisfied that it is necessary or expedient so to do, it may, by`
  line `notification, amend the First Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (80948)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Power of court or tribunal to refer parties to mediation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80948&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding the nonsettlement of dispute under sub-section (1) of section 5, the court or tribunal may, at any stage of`
  line `proceeding, refer the parties to undertake mediation.`
  line
  line `(2) If the court or tribunal refers the parties to undertake mediation, it may pass suitable interim`
  line `order to protect the interest of any party if deemed appropriate.`
  line
  line `(3) The parties shall not be under obligation to come to a settlement in the mediation pursuant to a`
  line `reference under sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (80949)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Appointment of mediators.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80949&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Unless otherwise agreed upon by the parties, a person of any`
  line `nationality may be appointed as a mediator:`
  line
  line `Provided that mediator of any foreign nationality shall possess such qualification, experience and`
  line `accreditation as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(2) The parties shall be free to agree upon the name of mediator and the procedure for their`
  line appointment.
  line
  line `(3) If the parties do not reach any agreement on a matter referred to in sub-section (2), then the`
  line `party seeking initiation of mediation shall make an application to a mediation service provider for the`
  line `appointment of a mediator.`
  line
  line `(4) Upon receiving an application under sub-section (3), the mediation service provider shall,`
  line `within a period of seven days, appoint, --`
  line
  line `(i) the mediator as agreed by the parties; or`
  line
  line `(ii) in case the parties are unable to reach agreement as to the appointment of mediator or`
  line `mediator agreed by them refuses to act as mediator, a mediator from the panel maintained by it,`
  line `with his consent.`
  line
  line `(5) The person appointed under clause (i) of sub-section (4) shall communicate his willingness or`
  line `otherwise within a period of seven days from the date of receipt of communication of such`
  line appointment.
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (80950)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Preference of parties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80950&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The mediation service provider shall, while appointing any person from`
  line `the panel of mediators maintained by it, consider his suitability and the preference of the parties for`
  line `resolving the dispute.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (80951)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Conflict of interest and disclosure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80951&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The person appointed as a mediator shall, prior to the`
  line `conduct of mediation, disclose in writing to the parties regarding any circumstance or potential`
  line `circumstance, personal, professional, financial, or otherwise, that may constitute any conflict of`
  line `interest or that is likely to give rise to justifiable doubts as to his independence or impartiality as a`
  line mediator.
  line
  line `(2) During the mediation, the mediator shall, without delay, disclose to the parties in writing any`
  line `conflict of interest, referred to in sub-section (1), that has newly arisen or has come to his knowledge.`
  line
  line `(3) Upon disclosure under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), the parties shall have the option to`
  line `waive any objection if all of them express in writing, which shall be construed as the consent of`
  line parties.
  line
  line `(4) Upon disclosure under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), if either party desires to replace the`
  line `mediator, then, in case of--`
  line
  line `(i) institutional mediation, such party shall apply to the mediation service provider for`
  line `termination of the mandate of mediator;`
  line
  line `(ii) mediation other than institutional mediation, such party shall terminate the mandate of`
  line mediator.
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (80952)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Termination of mandate of mediator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80952&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `A mediation service provider may terminate the`
  line `mandate of a mediator upon--`
  line
  line `(i) the receipt of application from a party under clause (i) of sub-section (4) of section 10; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the receipt of information about the mediator being involved in a matter of conflict of`
  line `interest from participants or any other person; or`
  line
  line `(iii) his withdrawal from mediation for any reason:`
  line
  line `Provided that termination under clause (ii) shall be effected if, after giving a hearing to the`
  line `mediator, mediation service provider finds that there is justifiable doubt as to the independence or`
  line `impartiality of the mediator and that the same has been brought to the notice of parties and that`
  line `either party desires to replace the mediator.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (80953)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Replacement of mediator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80953&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Upon termination of the mandate of mediator--`
  line
  line `(i) in case of mediation other than institutional mediation under clause (ii) of sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 10, the parties may, appoint another mediator within a period of seven days from such`
  line `termination; and`
  line
  line `(ii) under section 11, the mediation service provider shall appoint another mediator from the panel`
  line `maintained by it within a period of seven days from such termination.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (80954)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Territorial jurisdiction to undertake mediation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80954&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Every mediation under this Act shall be`
  line `undertaken within the territorial jurisdiction of the court or tribunal of competent jurisdiction to decide`
  line `the subject matter of dispute:`
  line
  line `Provided that on the mutual consent of the parties, mediation may be conducted at any place`
  line `outside the territorial jurisdiction of the court or tribunal, or by way of online mediation.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the removal of doubts, it is clarified that where the parties agree to conduct the`
  line `mediation at any place outside the territorial jurisdiction or online, for the purpose of enforcement,`
  line `challenge and registration of the mediated settlement agreement, the same shall be deemed to have`
  line `been undertaken within the territorial jurisdiction of the court or tribunal of competent jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (80955)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Commencement of mediation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80955&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The mediation proceedings with respect to a particular`
  line `dispute shall be deemed to have commenced---`
  line
  line `(a) where there is an existing agreement between the parties to settle the dispute through`
  line `mediation, the date on which a party or parties receives notice from the party initiating the mediation,`
  line `to refer such dispute to mediation; or`
  line
  line `(b) in other cases---`
  line
  line `(i) where the parties have agreed to appoint a mediator of their choice for mediation and`
  line `settlement of disputes between them on the date the mediator provides his consent to`
  line `appointment; or`
  line
  line `(ii) where one of the parties applies to a mediation service provider for settlement of disputes`
  line `through mediation, the date of appointment of a mediator.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (80956)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Conduct of mediation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80956&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The mediation process shall be conducted in the manner as may`
  line `be specified.`
  line
  line `(2) The mediator shall assist the parties in an independent, neutral and impartial manner in their`
  line `attempt to reach an amicable settlement of their dispute.`
  line
  line `(3) The mediator shall at all times be guided by the principles of objectivity and fairness and`
  line `protect the voluntariness, confidentiality and self-determination of the parties, and the standards for`
  line `professional and ethical conduct as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(4) The mediation process may include the mediator taking such measures as may be considered`
  line `appropriate, taking into account the circumstances of the case, including meeting with parties or`
  line `participants, jointly or separately, as frequently as deemed fit by the mediator, both in order to`
  line `convene the mediation, and during the mediation for the orderly and timely conduct of the process and`
  line `to maintain its integrity.`
  line
  line `(5) The mediator shall not be bound by the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), or the`
  line `Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872).`
  line
  line `(6) The mediator with the consent of the parties shall determine the language or languages to be`
  line `used in the mediation process`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (80957)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Role of mediator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80957&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The mediator shall attempt to facilitate voluntary resolution of the`
  line `dispute by the parties and communicate the view of each party to the other to the extent agreed to by`
  line `them, assist them in identifying issues, advancing better understanding, clarifying priorities, exploring`
  line `areas of the responsibility of the parties to take decision regarding their claims.`
  line
  line `(2) The parties shall be informed expressly by the mediator that he only facilitates in arriving at a`
  line `decision to resolve a dispute and that he shall not impose any settlement nor give any assurance that`
  line `the mediation may result in a settlement.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (80958)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Role of mediator in other proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80958&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The mediator shall not--`
  line
  line `(a) act as an arbitrator or as a representative or counsel of a party in any arbitral or judicial`
  line `proceeding in respect of a dispute that is the subject matter of the mediation proceedings;`
  line
  line `(b) be presented by the parties as a witness in any arbitral or judicial proceeding.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (80959)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Time-limit for completion of mediation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80959&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, mediation under this Act shall be completed within a period of`
  line `one hundred and twenty days from the date fixed for the first appearance before the mediator.`
  line
  line `(2) The period for mediation mentioned under sub-section (1) may be extended for a further period`
  line `as agreed by the parties, but not exceeding sixty days.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (80960)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Mediated settlement agreement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80960&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) A mediated settlement agreement includes an`
  line `agreement in writing between some or all of the parties resulting from mediation, settling some or all`
  line `of the disputes between such parties, and authenticated by the mediator:`
  line
  line `Provided that the terms of the mediated settlement agreement may extend beyond the disputes`
  line `referred to mediation.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- A mediated settlement agreement which is void under the Indian Contract Act,`
  line `1872 (9 of 1872), shall not be deemed to be lawful settlement agreement within the meaning of`
  line `mediated settlement agreement.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a mediated settlement agreement is reached between the parties with regard to all or`
  line `some of the disputes, the same shall be reduced in to writing and signed by the parties.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of section 26, the mediated settlement agreement signed,--`
  line
  line `(i) in case of institutional mediation, shall be submitted to the mediator, who shall, after`
  line `authenticating the same, forward it with a covering letter signed by him, to the mediation service`
  line `provider and also provide a copy to the parties;`
  line
  line `(ii) in all other cases, shall be submitted to the mediator who shall, after authenticating the`
  line `mediated settlement agreement, provide a copy to all the parties.`
  line
  line `(4) The parties, may, at any time during the mediation process, make an agreement with respect to`
  line `any of the disputes which is the subject matter of mediation.`
  line
  line `(5) Any mediated settlement agreement under this section includes a settlement agreement resulting`
  line `from online mediation.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (80962)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Registration of mediated settlement agreement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80962&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of record, mediated`
  line `settlement agreement arrived at between the parties, other than those arrived in a court or tribunal`
  line `referred mediation or award of Lok Adalat or final award of the Permanent Lok Adalat under`
  line `section 21 or section 22E of the Legal Services Authorities Act, 1987 (39 of 1987), may, at the option`
  line `of parties, be registered with an Authority constituted under the said Act, or any other body as may be`
  line `notified by the Central Government, in such manner as may be specified and such Authority or body`
  line `shall issue a unique registration number to such settlement agreements:`
  line
  line `Provided that the mediated settlement agreement under this section may be registered with such`
  line `Authority or the body situated within the territorial jurisdiction of the court or tribunal of competent`
  line `jurisdiction to decide the subject matter of dispute.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is clarified that nothing contained in this sub-section`
  line `shall affect the rights of parties to enforce the mediated settlement agreement under section 27 or`
  line `challenge the same under section 28.`
  line
  line `(2) The registration referred to in sub-section (1) may be made by the parties or mediation service`
  line `provider within a period of one hundred and eighty days from the date of receipt of authenticated copy`
  line `of mediated settlement agreement:`
  line
  line `Provided that mediated settlement agreement may be allowed to be registered after the expiry of`
  line `period of one hundred and eighty days on payment of such fee as may be specified in consultation`
  line `with the Authority or any other body referred to in sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (80963)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Non-settlement report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80963&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of section 26, where no agreement is`
  line `arrived at between the parties, within the time period as provided under section 18, or where, the`
  line `mediator is of the view that no settlement is possible, he shall, --`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of institutional mediation, submit a non-settlement report to the mediation service`
  line `provider in writing;`
  line
  line `(ii) in all other cases, prepare a non-settlement report and provide a signed copy to all the parties:`
  line
  line `Provided that the report referred to in this section shall not disclose the cause of non- settlement, or`
  line `any other matter or thing referring to their conduct, during mediation.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (80964)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title Confidentiality.
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80964&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the other provisions of this Act, the mediator, mediation`
  line `service provider, the parties and participants in the mediation shall keep confidential all the following`
  line `matters relating to the mediation proceedings, namely: --`
  line
  line `(i) acknowledgements, opinions, suggestions, promises, proposals, apologies and admissions made`
  line `during the mediation;`
  line
  line `(ii) acceptance of, or willingness to, accept proposals made or exchanged in the mediation;`
  line
  line `(iii) documents prepared solely for the conduct of mediation or in relation thereto;`
  line
  line `(iv) any other mediation communication.`
  line
  line `(2) No audio or video recording of the mediation proceedings shall be made or maintained by the`
  line `parties or the participants including the mediator and mediation service provider, whether conducted in`
  line `person or online to ensure confidentiality of the conduct of mediation proceedings.`
  line
  line `(3) No party to the mediation shall in any proceeding before a court or tribunal including arbitral`
  line `tribunal, rely on or introduce as evidence any information or communication set forth in clauses (i) to`
  line `(iv) of sub-section (1), including any information in electronic form, or verbal communication and the`
  line `court or tribunal including arbitral tribunal shall not take cognizance of such information or evidence.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of this section shall not prevent the mediator from compiling or disclosing`
  line `general information concerning matters that have been subject of mediation, for research, reporting or`
  line `training purposes, if the information does not expressly or indirectly identify a party or participants or`
  line `the specific disputes in the mediation.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that nothing contained in this`
  line `section shall apply to the mediated settlement agreement where its disclosure is necessary for the`
  line `purpose of registration, enforcement and challenge.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (80965)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Admissibility and privilege against disclosure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80965&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) No mediator or participant in the`
  line `mediation, including experts and advisers engaged for the purpose of the mediation and persons`
  line `involved in the administration of the mediation, shall at any time be permitted, or compelled to`
  line `disclose to any court or tribunal, or in any adjudicatory proceedings, by whatever description, any`
  line `communication in mediation, or to state the contents or conditions of any document or nature or conduct of parties during mediation including the content of negotiations or offers or counter offers`
  line `with which they have become acquainted during the mediation:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section and section 22 shall protect from disclosure, information`
  line `sought or provided to prove or dispute a claim or complaint of professional misconduct of mediator or`
  line `malpractice based on conduct occurring during the mediation.`
  line
  line `(2) There shall be no privilege or confidentiality that will attach to--`
  line
  line `(a) a threat or statement of a plan to commit an offence punishable under any law for the`
  line `time being in force;`
  line
  line `(b) information relating to domestic violence or child abuse; and`
  line
  line `(c) statements made during a mediation showing a significant imminent threat to public`
  line `health or safety.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (80966)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Termination of mediation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80966&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `The mediation proceedings under this Act shall be deemed to`
  line terminate---
  line
  line `(a) on the date of signing and authentication of the mediated settlement agreement; or`
  line
  line `(b) on the date of the written declaration of the mediator, after consultation with the parties or`
  line `otherwise, to the effect that further efforts at mediation are no longer justified; or`
  line
  line `(c) on the date of the communication by a party or parties in writing, addressed to the mediator`
  line `and the other parties to the effect that the party wishes to opt out of mediation;`
  line
  line `(d) on the expiry of time limit under section 18.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (80967)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Cost of mediation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80967&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The cost of mediation, other than community mediation shall be`
  line `such as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(2) Unless otherwise agreed by the parties, all costs of mediation, including the fees of the`
  line `mediator and the charges of the mediation service provider shall be borne equally by the parties.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (80968)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Proceedings of Lok Adalat and Permanent Lok Adalat not to be affected.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80968&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line The
  line `provisions of this Act shall not apply to the proceedings conducted by Lok Adalat and Permanent Lok`
  line `Adalat under the Legal Services Authorities Act, 1987 (39 of 1987).`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (80969)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Enforcement of mediated settlement agreement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80969&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) A mediated settlement agreement`
  line `resulting from a mediation signed by the parties and authenticated by the mediator shall be final and`
  line `binding on the parties and persons claiming under them respectively and enforceable as per the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of section 28, the mediated settlement agreement shall be enforced in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), in the same manner`
  line `as if it were a judgment or decree passed by a court, and may, accordingly, be relied on by any of the`
  line `parties or persons claiming through them, by way of defence, set off or otherwise in any legal`
  line proceeding.
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (80970)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Challenge to mediated settlement agreement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80970&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `any other law for the time being in force, in any case in which the mediated settlement agreement is`
  line `arrived at between the parties and is sought to be challenged by either of the parties, such party may`
  line `file an application before the court or tribunal of competent jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(2) A mediated settlement agreement may be challenged only on all or any of the following`
  line `grounds, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) fraud;`
  line
  line `(ii) corruption;`
  line
  line `(iii) impersonation;`
  line
  line `(iv) where the mediation was conducted in disputes or matters not fit for mediation under`
  line `section 6.`
  line
  line `(3) An application for challenging the mediated settlement agreement shall not be made after ninety`
  line `days have elapsed from the date on which the party making that application has received the copy of`
  line `mediated settlement agreement under sub-section (3) of section 19:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the court or tribunal, as the case may be, is satisfied that the applicant was`
  line `prevented by sufficient cause from making the application within the said period of ninety days, it may`
  line `entertain the application within a further period of ninety days.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (80971)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title Limitation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80971&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Limitation Act, 1963 (36 of 1963) or`
  line `in any other law for the time being in force, in computing the period of limitation fixed for any`
  line `proceeding relating to disputes in respect of which a mediation has been undertaken under this Act, the`
  line `period from the date of commencement of mediation under section 14, and up to,--`
  line
  line `(i) submission of report under section 21; or`
  line
  line `(ii) termination of mediation under section 24, shall be excluded.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (80972)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Online mediation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80972&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) Online mediation including pre-litigation mediation may be conducted`
  line `at any stage of mediation under this Act, with the written consent of the parties including by the use of`
  line `electronic form or computer networks but not limited to an encrypted electronic mail service, secure`
  line `chat rooms or conferencing by video or audio mode or both.`
  line
  line `(2) The process of online mediation shall be in such manner as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(3) The conduct of online mediation shall be in the circumstances, which ensure that the essential`
  line `elements of integrity of proceedings and confidentiality are maintained at all times and the mediator`
  line `may take such appropriate steps in this regard as he deems fit.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the other provisions of this Act, the mediation communications in the case of online`
  line `mediation shall, ensure confidentiality of mediation.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (80973)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Establishment and incorporation of Mediation Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80973&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government`
  line `shall, by notification, establish for the purposes of this Act, a Council to be known as the Mediation`
  line `Council of India to perform the duties and discharge the functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid, having perpetual succession and`
  line `a common seal, with power, subject to the provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold and dispose of`
  line `property, both movable and immovable, and to enter into contract, and shall, by the said name, sue or`
  line `be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The head office of the Council shall be at Delhi or at such other place as may be notified by`
  line `the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The Council may, in consultation with the Central Government, establish offices at other`
  line `places in India and abroad.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (80974)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Composition of Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Notification No. S.O. 4506(E), for "Member" (w.e.f. 13-10-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80974&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall consist of the following members,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a person of ability, integrity and standing having adequate knowledge and professional`
  line `experience or shown capacity in dealing with problems relating to law, alternative dispute resolution`
  line `preferably mediation, public affairs or administration to be appointed by the Central Government---Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(b) a person having knowledge and experience in law related to mediation or alternative dispute`
  line `resolution mechanisms, to be appointed by the Central Government---Member;`
  line
  line `(c) an eminent person having experience in research or teaching in the field of mediation and`
  line `alternative dispute resolution laws, to be appointed by the Central Government---Member;`
  line
  line `(d) Secretary to the Government of India in the Department of Legal Affairs, Ministry of Law`
  line `and Justice or his representative not below the rank of Joint Secretary---Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) Secretary to the Government of India in the Department of Expenditure, Ministry of Finance`
  line `or his representative not below the rank of Joint Secretary---Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(f) Chief Executive Officer---Member-Secretary, ex officio; and`
  line
  line `(g) one representative of a recognised body of commerce and industry, chosen by the Central`
  line `Government--Part-Time Member.`
  line
  line `(2) The Members of the Council, other than ex officio members, shall hold office as such, for a`
  line `term of four years from the date on which they enter upon their office and shall be eligible for`
  line `re-appointment:`
  line
  line `Provided that no Member other than ex officio Member shall hold office after he has attained the`
  line `age of seventy years, in the case of Chairperson, and sixty-seven years, in the case of other Members:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if the Chairperson is appointed on Part-Time basis, then, at least one of the`
  line `Members appointed under clauses (b) or (c) shall be a Full---Time Member.`
  line
  line `(3) The salaries, allowances and other terms and conditions of Members other than ex officio`
  line `Members shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The ^1[Part-Time Member] shall be entitled to such travelling and other allowances as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (80975)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate proceedings of Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80975&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceeding of the`
  line `Council shall be invalid merely by reason of--`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy or any defect, in the constitution of the Council;`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the appointment of a person as a Member of the Council; or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in the procedure of the Council not affecting the merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (80976)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title Resignation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80976&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `The Member may, by notice in writing, under his hand addressed to the Central`
  line `Government, resign his office:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Member shall, unless he is permitted by the Central Government to relinquish his`
  line `office sooner, continue to hold office until the expiry of three months from the date of receipt of such`
  line `notice or until a person duly appointed as his successor enters upon his office or until the expiry of his`
  line `term of office, whichever is earlier.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (80977)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title Removal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80977&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, remove any Member from his office, if he--`
  line
  line `(a) is an undischarged insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(b) has engaged at any time, during his term of office, in any paid employment without the`
  line `permission of the Central Government; or`
  line
  line `(c) has been convicted of an offence which, in the opinion of the Central Government, involves`
  line `moral turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(d) has acquired such financial or other interest as is likely to affect prejudicially his functions as a`
  line `Member; or`
  line
  line `(e) has so abused his position as to render his continuance in office prejudicial to the public`
  line `interest; or`
  line
  line `(f) has become physically or mentally incapable of acting as a Member:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a Member is proposed to be removed on any ground, he shall be informed of`
  line `charges against him and given an opportunity of being heard in respect of those charges.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (80978)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Appointment of experts and constitution of Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80978&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `The Council may, appoint such`
  line `experts and constitute such committees of experts as it may consider necessary to discharge its`
  line `functions on such terms and conditions as may be specified.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (80979)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Secretariat and Chief Executive Officer of Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80979&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be a Chief Executive`
  line `Officer of the Council, who shall be responsible for the day to day administration and implementation`
  line `of the decisions of the Council.`
  line
  line `(2) The qualification, appointment and other terms and conditions of service of the Chief Executive`
  line `Officer shall be such as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(3) There shall be a Secretariat to the Council consisting of such number of officers and employees`
  line `as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(4) The qualification, appointment and other terms and conditions of the service of the employees`
  line `and other officers of the Council shall be such as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government shall provide such number of officers and employees as may be`
  line `necessary for the functioning of the Council till regulations are made under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (80980)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Duties and functions of Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80980&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `The Council shall--`
  line
  line `(a) endeavour to promote domestic and international mediation in India through appropriate`
  line guidelines;
  line
  line `(b) endeavour to develop India to be a robust centre for domestic and international mediation;`
  line
  line `(c) lay down the guidelines for the continuous education, certification and assessment of`
  line `mediators by the recognised mediation institutes;`
  line
  line `(d) provide for the manner of conduct of mediation proceedings, under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 15;`
  line
  line `(e) provide for manner of registration of mediators and renew, withdraw, suspend or cancel`
  line `registration on the basis of conditions as may be specified;`
  line
  line `(f) lay down standards for professional and ethical conduct of mediators under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 15;`
  line
  line `(g) hold trainings, workshops and courses in the area of mediation in collaboration with`
  line `mediation service providers, law firms and universities and other stakeholders, both Indian and`
  line `international, and any other mediation institutes;`
  line
  line `(h) enter into memoranda of understanding or agreements with domestic and international`
  line `bodies or organisations or institutions;`
  line
  line `(i) recognise mediation institutes and mediation service providers and renew, withdraw,`
  line `suspend or cancel such recognition;`
  line
  line `(j) specify the criteria for recognition of mediation institutes and mediation service providers;`
  line
  line `(k) call for any information or record of mediation institutes and mediation service providers;`
  line
  line `(l) lay down standards for professional and ethical conduct of the mediation institutes and`
  line `mediation service providers;`
  line
  line `(m) publish such information, data, research studies and such other information as may be`
  line required;
  line
  line `(n) maintain an electronic depository of the mediated settlement agreements made in India and`
  line `for such other records related thereto in such manner as may be specified; and`
  line
  line `(o) perform any other function as may be assigned to it by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (80981)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Monitoring and reporting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80981&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall, as soon as practicable after the end of each`
  line `year or at such other intervals as directed by the Central Government, prepare a report on the`
  line `implementation of the provisions of this Act during the year or such interval and forward a copy`
  line `thereof to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may take such additional measures as it deems necessary to`
  line `supplement the functioning of the Council and for the effective implementation of the provisions of`
  line `the Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (80982)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Mediation service provider.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80982&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) "mediation service provider" includes--`
  line
  line `(a) a body or an organisation that provides for the conduct of mediation under this Act and the`
  line `rules and regulations made thereunder and is recognised by the Council; or`
  line
  line `(b) an Authority constituted under the Legal Services Authorities Act, 1987 (39 of 1987); or`
  line
  line `(c) a court-annexed mediation centre; or`
  line
  line `(d) any other body as may be notified by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the bodies referred to in clauses (b), (c) and (d) shall be deemed to be mediation`
  line `service providers recognised by the Council.`
  line
  line `(2) The mediation service provider shall be recognised by the Council in the manner as`
  line `may be specified.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (80983)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Functions of mediation service providers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80983&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `The mediation service providers shall perform`
  line `the following functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) accredit mediators and maintain panel of mediators;`
  line
  line `(b) provide the services of mediator for conduct of mediation;`
  line
  line `(c) provide all facilities, secretarial assistance and infrastructure for the efficient conduct of`
  line mediation;
  line
  line `(d) promote professional and ethical conduct amongst mediators;`
  line
  line `(e) facilitate registration of mediated settlement agreements in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `section 20; and`
  line
  line `(f) such other functions as may be specified.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (80984)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Mediation institutes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80984&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `The Council shall recognize mediation institutes to perform such`
  line `duties and exercise such functions as may be specified.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (80985)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Community mediation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80985&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any dispute likely to affect peace, harmony and tranquillity`
  line `amongst the residents or families of any area or locality may be settled through community mediation`
  line `with prior mutual consent of the parties to the dispute.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1), any of the parties shall make an application before the`
  line `concerned Authority constituted under the Legal Services Authorities Act, 1987 (39 of 1987) or`
  line `District Magistrate or Sub-Divisional Magistrate in areas where no such Authority has been`
  line `constituted, for referring the dispute to mediation.`
  line
  line `(3) In order to facilitate settlement of a dispute for which an application has been received under`
  line `sub-section (2), the concerned Authority constituted under the Legal Services Authorities Act, 1987`
  line `(39 of 1987) or the District Magistrate or Sub-Divisional Magistrate, as the case may be, shall`
  line `constitute panel of three community mediators.`
  line
  line `(4) For the purposes of this section, the Authority or District Magistrate or the Sub-Divisional`
  line `Magistrate, as the case may be, shall notify a permanent panel of community mediators, which may be`
  line `revised from time to time..`
  line
  line `(5) The following persons may be included in the panel referred to in sub-section (4)---`
  line
  line `(a) person of standing and integrity who are respectable in the community;`
  line
  line `(b) any local person whose contribution to the society has been recognised;`
  line
  line `(c) representative of area or resident welfare associations;`
  line
  line `(d) person having experience in the field of mediation; and`
  line
  line `(e) any other person deemed appropriate.`
  line
  line `(6) While making panel referred to in sub-section (4) the representation of women or any other`
  line `class or category of persons may be considered.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (80986)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Procedure for community mediation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80986&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any community mediation shall be conducted by`
  line `the panel of three community mediators referred to in sub-section (3) of section 43 who shall devise`
  line `suitable procedure for the purpose of resolving the dispute.`
  line
  line `(2) The community mediators shall endeavour to resolve disputes through community mediation`
  line `and provide assistance to parties for resolving disputes amicably.`
  line
  line `(3) In every case where a settlement agreement is arrived at through community mediation under`
  line `this Act, the same may be reduced into writing with the signature of the parties and authenticated by`
  line `the community mediators, a copy of which be provided to the parties and in cases where no settlement`
  line `agreement is arrived at, a non-settlement report may be submitted by the community mediators to the`
  line `Authority or the District Magistrate or the Sub-Divisional Magistrate, as the case may be, and to the`
  line parties.
  line
  line `(4) Any settlement agreement arrived at under this Chapter shall be for the purpose of maintaining`
  line `the peace, harmony and tranquillity amongst the residents or families of any area or locality but shall`
  line `not be enforceable as a judgment or decree of a civil court.`
  line
  line `(5) The provisions of section 20 shall, mutatis mutandis apply, in relation to the registration of`
  line `mediated settlement agreement under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (80988)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Mediation Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80988&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be a fund to be called “Mediation Fund” (hereinafter`
  line `referred to as the “Fund”) for the purposes of promotion, facilitation and encouragement of mediation`
  line `under this Act, which shall be administered by the Council.`
  line
  line `(2) There shall be credited to the Fund the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) all monies provided by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) all fees and other charges received from mediation service provider, mediation institutes or`
  line `bodies or persons;`
  line
  line `(c) all monies received by the Council in the form of donations, grants, contributions and`
  line `income from other sources;`
  line
  line `(d) grants made by the Central Government or the State Government for the purposes of the`
  line Fund;
  line
  line `(e) amounts deposited by persons as contributions to the Fund;`
  line
  line `(f) amounts received in the Fund from any other source; and`
  line
  line `(g) interest on the above or other income received out of the investment made from the Fund.`
  line
  line `(3) The Fund shall be applied towards meeting the salaries and other allowances of Member, Chief`
  line `Executive Officer, Officers and employees and the expenses of the Council including expenses`
  line `incurred in the exercise of its powers and discharge of its duties under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (80989)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80989&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant`
  line `records and prepare an annual statement of accounts, including the balance sheet, in such form and`
  line `manner as may be prescribed in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Council shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India`
  line `and any expenditure incurred by him in connection with such audit shall be payable by the Council to`
  line `the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any person appointed by him in connection`
  line `with the audit of the accounts of the Council shall have the same rights, privileges and authority in`
  line `connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India has in connection with the`
  line `audit of the Government accounts, and, in particular, shall have the right to demand the production of`
  line `books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect the offices of the`
  line Council.
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Council as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or any`
  line `other person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (80990)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Power of Central Government to issue directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80990&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the foregoing`
  line `provisions of this Act, the Council shall, in exercise of its powers or the performance of its functions`
  line `under this Act, be bound by such directions on questions of policy as the Central Government may`
  line `give in writing to it from time to time:`
  line
  line `Provided that the views of the Council shall be taken into consideration before any direction is`
  line `given under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) The decision of the Central Government whether a question is one of policy or not shall be`
  line final.
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (80991)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Power to frame schemes or guidelines.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80991&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Central`
  line `Government or the State Government or any of its entity or agency, as the case may be, may frame any`
  line `schemes or guidelines, for resolution of any dispute through mediation or conciliation in cases where`
  line `the Central Government or the State Government or any of its entity or agency is one of the parties`
  line `and in such cases mediation or conciliation may be conducted in accordance with such schemes or`
  line guidelines.
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (80992)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Mediated settlement agreement where Government or its, agency, etc., is a party.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80992&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, no dispute including a commercial dispute,`
  line `wherein the Central Government or State Government or any of its agencies, public bodies,`
  line `corporations and local bodies including entities controlled or owned by them is a party, the settlement`
  line `agreement arrived at shall be signed only after obtaining the prior written consent of the competent`
  line `authority of such Government or any of its entity or agencies, public bodies, corporations and local`
  line `bodies, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (80993)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80993&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Central Government or a State Government or any officer of such Government, or the`
  line `Member or Officer or employee of the Council or a mediator, mediation institutes, mediation service`
  line `providers, which is done or is intended to be done in good faith under this Act or the rules or`
  line `regulations made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (80994)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Notification No. S.O. 4506(E), for "Member" (w.e.f. 13-10-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80994&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make rules for`
  line `carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `make provision for--`
  line
  line `(a) the salaries and allowances and the terms and conditions of the Members under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 32;`
  line
  line `(b) the travelling and other allowances payable to the ^1[Part-Time Member] under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 32;`
  line
  line `(c) the form and manner of annual statement of accounts, including the balance sheet under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 46; and`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter which is to be, or may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (80995)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80995&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council may, with the previous approval of the Central`
  line `Government, by notification, make regulations consistent with this Act and the rules made thereunder`
  line `to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations`
  line `may make provision for--`
  line
  line `(a) qualification, experience and accreditation for mediators of foreign nationality under the`
  line `proviso to sub-section (1) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(b) manner of conducting mediation proceeding under sub-section (1) of section15;`
  line
  line `(c) standards for professional and ethical conduct of mediators under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 15;`
  line
  line `(d) manner of registration of mediated settlement agreement under sub-section (1) of section 20;`
  line
  line `(e) fees for registration of mediated settlement agreement under the proviso to sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 20;`
  line
  line `(f) cost of mediation under sub-section (1) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(g) manner of process of conducting online mediation under sub-section (2) of section 30;`
  line
  line `(h) the terms and conditions of experts and committees of experts under section 36;`
  line
  line `(i) qualifications, appointment and other terms and conditions of service of the Chief Executive`
  line `Officer under sub-section (2) of section 37;`
  line
  line `(j) the number of officers and employees of the Secretariat of the Council under sub-section (3)`
  line `of section 37;`
  line
  line `(k) the qualification, appointment and other terms and conditions of the employees and other`
  line `officers of the Council under sub-section (4) of section 37;`
  line
  line `(l) conditions for registration of mediators and renewal, withdrawal, suspension or cancellations`
  line `of such registrations under clause (e) of section 38;`
  line
  line `(m) criteria for recognition of mediation institutes and mediation service providers under`
  line `clause (j) of section 38;`
  line
  line `(n) manner of maintenance of electronic depository of mediated settlement agreement under`
  line `clause (n) of section 38;`
  line
  line `(o) manner for recognition of mediation service provider under sub-section (2) of section 40;`
  line
  line `(p) such other functions of mediation service provider under clause (f) of section 41;`
  line
  line `(q) duties and functions to be performed by mediation institutes under section 42; and`
  line
  line `(r) any other matter in respect of which provision is necessary for the performance of functions`
  line `of the Council under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (80996)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title Laying.
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80996&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `Every notification issued under sub-section (2) of section 6, sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 55, rule and regulation made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is issued or`
  line `made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the notification, rule or regulation or both Houses agree that the`
  line `notification, rule or regulation should not be issued or made, the notification, rule or regulation shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however,`
  line `that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything`
  line `previously done under that notification, rule or regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (80997)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80997&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such`
  line `provisions, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as may appear to it to be necessary for`
  line `removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made under this section after the expiry of a period of five`
  line `years from the date of commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under sub-section (1) shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before`
  line `each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (81001)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Provisions of Act to have overriding effect on mediation or conciliation contained in other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=81001&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the enactments mentioned in the Second Schedule, the provisions of this Act`
  line `shall have overriding effect for conduct of mediation or conciliation notwithstanding anything`
  line `inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being in force, and any instrument`
  line `having force of law.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Central Government is satisfied that it is necessary or expedient so to do, it may, by`
  line `notification, amend the Second Schedule and thereupon it shall be deemed to have been amended`
  line accordingly.
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (80999)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Act not to apply to pending proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=80999&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `This Act shall not apply to, or in relation to, any`
  line `mediation or conciliation commenced before the coming into force of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (81000)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Transitory provision.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677&sectionId=81000&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00011_A2023-32_1697800640677
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `The rules in force governing the conduct of court-annexed mediation`
  line `shall continue to apply until regulations are made under sub-section (1) of section 15:`
  line
  line `Provided that the rules shall continue to apply in all court-annexed mediation pending as on the`
  line `date of coming into force of the regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
